The '''golden cuckooshrike''' ('''''Campochaera sloetii''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Campephagidae]]. It is [[monotypic]] within the genus '''''Campochaera'''''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Itis Report: ''Campochaera'' |url=https://www.itis.gov/servlet/SingleRpt/SingleRpt?search_topic=TSN&search_value=557480 |access-date=12 June 2012 |publisher=Integrated Taxonomic Information System}}</ref> It is found in [[New Guinea]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or [[tropical]] moist lowland [[forest]]s.

